<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Aldur on 06-16-2000 08:11 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Well I have to say that a free heal every 6 seconds is a little unbalanced dont ya think?

how many other classes can meditate what 90 mana in one tick.

They always said the cast times were 3-4x normal hence if anything they were unbalanced before.

The shaman arms are very very unbalanced I heard of what you can do with them so I don't expect them to be untouched for very long.

in my opinion from all equipment I seen if a peice of equipment changes radically what you are capable of doing then it will get changed.  Items on the whole just let you do what you do a bit better.

Some of the best items (EM BP, alabone gorget) and such don't actually let the cleric suddenly take on the world and win.  

It seems that having these effects on the armour is a bit of a mistake by verant.  Either its a completely worthless spell and people complain (bard summon food/water effects) or they are too powerful and is a must have item.

good spells to have on items are ones that people still use at level 50-60.  Having sow on druid and shaman armour, snare on ranger and druid armour that type of thing.  Maybe having level 49 ress spell on cleric BP with cast time of around a minute.  It wont let us take on red mobs and win but it will stop us sitting about on our arses all day ressing after a bad raid.

Things that people use day in day out but having something that would radically change the way you work (darkness on that necklace is one....has it been nerfed? cos a cleric with snare is so powerful - and no its not particually because im jealous (even though I am heh) its the fact that movement slowdown spells are something we have never had before....giving us that skill would definitely infringe on other classes role in a group).</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
